nts1.d: Writer, historian and DJ Bill Brewster showcasing two hours of love, laughter, and music.
Settle in for weekly shows from Margeaux aka @marg.mp3, soothing with an hour of selections, offering an eclectic range of sounds old and new.

TRiNH - an hour of covers and nostalgic feels, playing a wide range of genres with a focus on L-O-V-E.

nts1.n: QUEST NO MORE W/ ELHEIST & MTMBO
nts1.d: Elheist steers deep‑cuts, left‑field electronica, obscure grooves and sounds from the fam into the fold, where worlds collide, textures shift and surprises hit. check your quest, leave the rest.

ARTIST, DJ Cõvco sonically birthing a utopian place of chaku chaku. With her bi-monthly invitation, she explores her limitless approach to mixing, a soundclash of experimental/warped club beats mixed with her live melodic/chants acapella edits - her signature dancefloor experience.

nts1.n: SURF GANG RADIO W/ SAMBA JEAN-BAPTISTE
nts1.d: A radio show curated by Surf Gang Records.
Sounds from the grass roots of jungle and drum & bass with London scene heroes Rupture - featuring selections from residents Mantra & Double O.
Bristol based Londoner and Soft Raw label owner Danielle, takes over for an hour a month, running through a broad spectrum of dance music - from ambient to leftfield, techno, electro & beyond.
Th4ys brings the raw energy of Brazil’s funk scene to the airwaves—a space for self-expression, representation, and true community.

Elena Colombi helps to keep nights weird - expect a diverse range of up-and-at-'em records: from techno to post-punk, through EBM, industrial and -wave…
From the host: "Celebrating 10 years on the station!!!
With a nod to the genres I explored on my very first show.
A proper mixed bag."

nts2.n: GREAT SOUTHERN LANDS W/ JAMES W
nts2.d: Recorded live from Naarm/Melbourne, Great Southern Lands is an excursion through the deep Australian and New Zealand underground. Expect post-VU freakouts, dolewave jangles, forgotten lathe-cuts and avant-garde chin scratchers, served up by a bunch of Antipodean amateurs.

Broadcasting out of Birmingham, Arrhythmia is a monthly exploration of interesting new audio and abnormal rhythms. Expect irregular, dark or heavy - but not always.
From the host: "A Best of 2025 show featuring Abdullah Miniawy, X-Cetra, Haress, Alpha Maid, Smote and a ton more."

The Parisian selector Guigio Jiolua returns with a one-off sunrise guest episode. 
"This mix was recorded in the early morning hours at a best friend’s birthday party, on the beautiful shores of Normandy. It might not sound like a party, but it truly was."
Kaifeng based DJ & producer Yu Su cooks up an hour of warm meanderings once a month.
The breezy sound of the Canadian Riviera, from Mood Hut's Pender Street Steppers.
Brooklyn musician Nick Hakim takes over the NTS airwaves.
"A mix for forest bathing on dark winter days."
Ahwlee & Pink Siifu (B. Cool-Aid) head up BRWN, exploring hip hop's varied and far-reaching experimental corners - live once a month from Los Angeles.

West Coast Fog with Erik Bluhm, broadcasts monthly from far-flung natural environments, bringing along site specific, privately released meditational music from past decades for a deeply involved sensory experience.
From the host: "Climb up, slide down. Creep along the dragon's back and motivate with a soothing soundtrack of tapes and records from Sausalito, Nevada City, Idyllwild, Berkeley, and more."

Hosted by Mirage, founder of Dubversified Culture, a community-led organization focusing on music, art, and events. Mirage, originally from Québec, blends house and hip-hop since 2010, now exploring 140bpm and Deep D&B.

subtle.d: Potent Funk records’ Matt Frost - Well known for his technical abilities and Sleazy bass music style, Frost covers all angles from UK alt Rap to the LA beat scene.

subtle.n: Collectors' Cuts w/ Antek feat. Ben Boe

subtle.d: Get ready to embark on a captivating sonic journey of underground music with Charlie Kelly. Including new and timeless sounds from the depths of rap, drill, grime, and experimental genres from the vibrant streets of the UK and beyond. Charlie unearths the very best in music that pushes boundaries. Off the mic, Charlie is a Radio Producer and Social Media Executive with an eclectic music taste spanning across many different cultures, decades, and styles. Hailing from North London with a love for audio and pop culture, you can expect to hear tune after tune when you’re locked into Charlie Kelly on Subtle.
BirdE brings an hour of the freshest Drum and Bass covering everything from liquid to techy steppers - the deeper the better.

Originally from Cambridge, Counter Culture's selection deftly navigates across a myriad of influences and exclusives from himself & friends.
Expect some of the freshest rolling soul straight to your headspace.

Sometimes it gets dark, sometimes I try to mix techno awkwardly, sometimes i get nostalgic… I like stuff that’s dreamy, ghostly, pretty and sad. I’ll try out new productions of my own, as well. I’m keeping it pretty open and we’ll see how it evolves.” – Jimmy
